                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">I received your very kind letter of <date>10
                                                  Dec</date><lb/> am quite ashamed of not having
                                        acknowledged it before, but<lb/> the enclosed reflections
                                        must impart plead my excuse if they meet<lb/> your
                                        approbation at the time I received it I was also engaged
                                        in<lb/> writing to a clergyman who after a lapse of five
                                        years had the Grace<lb/> to answer a letter which I write to
                                        him on subjects connected with<lb/> our Holy religion.
                                        however I delivered your enclosed letter to our<lb/> friend
                                                  <persName>Mr I Lindo</persName> called on
                                                  <persName>Mrs Joel</persName> who said she had
                                        already<lb/> forwarded to you the statement you required. I
                                        also called on the<lb/> Publisher of the Jewish Chronicle
                                        who in as much surprised that<lb/> there should have been
                                        any irregularity in the delivery of the numbers<lb/> which
                                        he say were regularly posted every week he gave me the<lb/>
                                        enclosed order for a set of the Jewish Miscellany which he
                                        request<lb/> you to send at your earliest convenience he
                                        will pay the cost to <persName>Mrs<lb/> Joel</persName> or
                                        elsewhere as you may direct I have received the
                                        prospectus<lb/> of the works you propose engaging in should
                                        feel very happy if<lb/> I could contribute to your success,
                                        but I have already told you<lb/> what very little influence
                                        I possess in the nation what a reserved<lb/> life I lead I
                                        fear any application on my part for support to<lb/> your
                                        exertion <del>it</del> would be ineffectual be considered as
                                        a rem[?]<lb/> instance of my assurance put me down as a
                                        subscriber<lb/> to the Jewish advocateâ€“</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>I am glad you received the apocryphal New Testament I presume<lb/>
                                        <persName>Dr Raphael</persName> is correct in stating that
                                        the Publisher [?] was prosecuted<lb/> but I do not think it
                                        could have been for this publication you will see<lb/> that
                                        several of the books have been translated published in the
                                        works<lb/> of learned men here. but I remember seeing in his
                                        shop windows in<lb/> fleet street an atrocious caricature of
                                        the almighty in which he was<lb/> depicted with all the
                                        figurative descriptions used in the Bible <lb/> at the foot
                                        "Christians Here is your God as by Law established"</p>
                              <p>I believe few persons had the audacity to enter the shop purchase
                                        it<lb/> I had not. I see the result of your interview with
                                                  <persName>Mr Knit</persName> his<lb/> reply that
                                        the synod had resolved to reply only to a Jewish
                                        assembly<lb/> of [?] not to an individual is very
                                        significant. however the ques<lb/>tion how my letter came to
                                        the hands of the publisher of the asmonean<lb/> will soon be
                                        solved for I see by the number for the week ending 20<lb/>
                                        decr (which the publisher politely sent me) that my letter
                                        was<lb/> sent to him by a Gentleman connected with the Synod
                                        accompanied<lb/> by an answer which on account of the [?] of
                                        the <sic>stile</sic> he did not<lb/> publish he proposed
                                        doing up shortly with a running commentary</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">If the answer is signed by the writer requires any
                                        other answer<lb/> than the commentary I shall perhaps take
                                        notice of it, but not if it<lb/> is anonymous perhaps you
                                        will say that my writings which you have<lb/> though worthy
                                        of a place in your interesting periodical has also been<lb/>
                                        anonymous by they have not been written to or at anybody but
                                        your<lb/> self to any inquirers you could always supply the
                                        name</p>
                              <p>I read with much pleasure your review of <persName>Dr
                                                  Raphel's</persName> lectures</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>I suppose he finds[...]<lb/> to print them I h[...]<lb/> nor have I
                                        ever heard [...]<lb/> abundance of material [...]<lb/>
